X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclair Foundation": "https://montclairfoundation.org/event/virtual-meditation-31-8/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclairfoundation_calendar_of_events
X-SOURCE:Montclair Foundation
X-SOURCE-URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T210000
DTSTAMP:20260317T224930
CREATED:20260224T215947Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T215948Z
UID:10006009-1773860400-1773867600@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Virtual Meditation
DESCRIPTION:Virtual Meditation \nInstructor: John Welshons \nWednesdays\, 7:00 PM – 9:00 PM \nJanuary 7\, 14\, 21\, 28 \nFebruary 4\, 11\, 25 \nMarch 11\, 18\, 25 \nApril 1\, 8\, 15\, 22\, 29 \nJoin contemporary spiritual teacher and author Ramananda John E. Welshons (One Soul\, One Love\, One Heart\, When Prayers Aren’t Answered and Awakening From Grief) for a series of evening meditation classes in the comfort of your own home via Zoom. These classes will focus on specific practices for working with fear and anxiety.  Participants will learn and practice different forms of mindfulness meditation in each session and will have the opportunity to participate in discussions of Ramananda’s three critically acclaimed books. Open to beginners and experienced practitioners\, these gatherings offer an opportunity to experience deep inner peace while practicing with a highly experienced meditation teacher.  \nImportant Updated Registration Information: \nA Zoom Link will be sent the day of the class. If you are registering after 3 PM on the day of the class\, the Zoom link will be included in the automated payment confirmation email sent when you register. There is no registration deadline for this class. \nFee: Single class: $10 Members / $15 General Public
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/virtual-meditation-31-8/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults,Virtual
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2024/06/outdoor-meditation-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclair Local News": "https://montclairlocal.news/event/special-screening-the-woman-of-stars-and-mountains/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclairlocal
X-SOURCE:Montclair Local News
X-SOURCE-URL:https://montclairlocal.news/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T210000
DTSTAMP:20260317T224928
CREATED:20260303T063427Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T063427Z
UID:10138194-1773860400-1773867600@montclairlocal.news
SUMMARY:Special Screening: THE WOMAN OF STARS AND MOUNTAINS
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, March 18 Only!\nRita\, an indigenous woman from Mexico\, left her Tarahumara mountain community in northern Mexico and embarked on a journey to Kansas. There\, she was involuntarily detained and confined in a psychiatric hospital for 12 years because the hospital authorities could not ascertain her identity\, origins\, or the language she spoke. Upon the discovery of the truth\, Rita returned to her community and her niece\, Juanita\, who cared for her. THE WOMAN OF STARS AND MOUNTAINS presents a moving portrait of Rita and explores the multiple forms of racism and discrimination that indigenous women face. \nA panel discussion and Q&A with Santiago Esteinou (Writer and Producer)\, Francisco G. Gómez (Co-Founder and Music Director of Raíces Cultural Center)\, Nicole Wines (Co-Founder and Director of Programming\, Communications and Technology of Raíces Cultural Center)\, moderated by Karin Jervert (Mad In the World Liaison from Mad In America Foundation) follows the screening. \nPresented in Partnership with MAD in America. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/special-screening-the-woman-of-stars-and-mountains/
