BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-ID:gcal_id8bbkkkfmscdavi2jilkb2muo
SUMMARY:Lenten Study "The Tears of Things - Wednesday evenings March 11\,1
 8\,25 @7:30pm on Zoom
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T203000
DTSTAMP:20260318T024952Z
UID:2j39bl8h8612qmbdairh547q80@google.com__20260318
SEQUENCE:1
CREATED:20260224T181527Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span>How do we live compassionately in a time of violence 
 and despair? What can we do with our private disappointments and the anger
  that we feel in such an unjust world? These are the questions many of us 
 carry on our hearts.  This Lent\, we will gather to explore them with Fra
 nciscan friar\,Richard Rohr\, as he turns to the writings of the Hebrew pr
 ophets to offer us a path forward today.<br><br>The prophets' writings ref
 lect the full spectrum of human maturity.  In almost every case their cri
 ticism of culture and institutions take them on a journey from anger to sa
 dness and ultimately\, to compassion. They confront evil and injustice in 
 a way that acknowledges the wholeness of history\, the interconnectedness 
 of every living being\, and the reality of divine and universal love.  In
  doing so\, they set the stage for Jesus\, who follows this identical patt
 ern. <br><br>This Lent\, join Rev. Ann for three Zoom sessions to explore
  what this ancient wisdom has to teach us in our own time of outrage and h
 eartbreak.<b><u><span> We encourage you to read the book to prepare for th
 is study.  You can order it online <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us
 6.list-manage.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=da482d4d86&e=
 d2d6ac503b" target="_blank"><span>HERE</span></a> or through your favorit
 e bookstore.</span></u></b> </span></p><p><b><span>To join the class clic
 k the</span></b><span> <a href="https://firstcongmontclair.us6.list-manag
 e.com/track/click?u=62bf2ca744bdb8b46fa1a7788&id=b628613b45&e=d2d6ac503b" 
 target="_blank"><span>ZOOM LINK HERE</span></a><br><br></span><b><span>We 
 look forward to taking this Lenten journey together.</span></b></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T181805Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
END:VEVENT
