UID:10006030-1773927000-1773930600@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:MILL Mini Fairy Gardens
DESCRIPTION:Partner Program with the Montclair Institute for Lifelong Learning \nWinter at Van Vleck \nThursdays\, 1:30 PM- 2:30 PM \n3/19 – Mini Fairy Gardens – Create your own enchanting mini fairy garden\, inspired by the whimsy of the Van Vleck Fairy Garden Trail.  Using natural elements and playful accents\, you’ll build a personal pint-sized haven to take home – perfect for inviting the fairies to come out and play. \nThis class is a Partner Program with the Montclair Institute for Lifelong Learning. To register please visit: http://schedulesplus.com/montclair/kiosk \nUpcoming class: \n3/26 – Beginner Birding Class – Learn how to identify common backyard birds by focusing on their characteristics\, behaviors and feeding habits. This informative session will be with a powerpoint and/or walk depending on the weather. Bring your own binoculars if you have them\, if not some will be provided.
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/mill-mini-fairy-gardens/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2026/01/20220325_145422-1-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
