SUMMARY:Hands-On Learning Takes Center Stage at the Montclair Public Library Auditorium: “Keyboard Fidgets” Workshop for NJ Makers Day
DESCRIPTION:The Montclair Public Library will join libraries and educational centers statewide in celebrating NJ Makers Day\, a three-day event highlighting creativity\, innovation\, and hands-on learning across New Jersey. This annual initiative invites residents of all ages to explore science\, technology\, engineering\, art\, and math (STEAM) through interactive projects and programs. \nAs part of this year’s celebration\, the library will host “Keyboard Fidgets”\, a program designed for tweens and teens to build a fun\, hands-on craft while learning basic design and assembly concepts. The program is sponsored by The Tutor Shack\, a Montclair based tutoring center dedicated to fostering curiosity and confidence in learners of all ages. \n“Maker education nurtures problem-solving\, creativity\, and collaboration. Skills that are essential for lifelong learning\,” said Steph Legnosky\, owner of The Tutor Shack. “We’re proud to support NJ Makers Day because it sparks imagination and empowers students to see themselves as creators and innovators. Partnering with the Montclair Public Library for events like this aligns perfectly with our mission to strengthen the foundations of learning through curiosity and exploration.” \nThe Keyboard Fidgets program will take place at the Montclair Public Library during NJ Makers Day weekend on Friday\, March 20 from 4:00 – 5:30 PM. Make your very own keyboard fidget keychain with amazing teen library volunteers! For ages 8 and up. Drop-in; while supplies last. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/hands-on-learning-takes-center-stage-at-the-montclair-public-library-auditorium-keyboard-fidgets-workshop-for-nj-makers-day/
LOCATION:Montclair Public Library\, 50 South Fullerton Avenue\, Montclair\, New Jersey\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:General Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://montclairlocal.news/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Montclair-Library-Makers-Day.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Public Library":MAILTO:publicrelations@montclair.bccls.org
END:VEVENT
