X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: Metrotrails Hiking": "https://www.meetup.com/metrotrails/events/313683110/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_metrotrails
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Metrotrails Hiking
UID:event_313683110@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260318T024945Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T084500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T104500
SUMMARY:Metrotrails 29 Year Anniversary Hike: Warren County!
DESCRIPTION:Metrotrails: NJ\, PA\, NY Metropolitan Area Hiking and More!\n
 Join us for our annual hike in Warren County\, marking 29 years since we b
 egan doing these hikes.\nI was still in high school for the first one\, an
 d we always did the old Warren Railroad.\nOver the years\, some properties
  became inaccessible\, unsafe\, or badly overgrown forcing us to change th
 e route we take. In some ways\, it's a good thing to cover some new ground
 \, and in others we miss some places we love.\nThis time\, we'll be follow
 ing some of the things we've done as well as some new stuff we've never in
 corporated into this hike previously.\nWe'll meet before 9 at the Port Col
 den Mall\, and then shuttle with as few vehicles as possible to our start 
 point.\nThis time\, we'll be out in the Pequest area for the beginning.\nS
 everal field trails make for a very pleasant way of starting.\nWe'll make 
 our way casually through all of these woods\, and then come to a short roa
 d walk in Townsbury to the Lehigh and Hudson River Railway grade.\nWe'll f
 ollow the L&HR west through Pequest and Buttzville\, then make our way on 
 road briefly to Hot Dog Johnny's for a probably late lunch.\nOnce finished
  at Johnny's\, we'll head up to the old Lackawanna/Warren Railroad in the 
 way we always walk back to Oxford.\nWhen we get to Oxford\, we'll make ref
 reshment stops\, and then head to the south. Rather than stay on the overg
 rown railroad bed\, we'll likely follow some back roads including Tunnel H
 ill Road through farm land where we'll see some different railroad remnant
 s\, then Jackson Valley Road back to 31. We'll finish our evening at the n
 ewly reopened Draught House to conclude the evening.\nIf needed\, contact 
 me at 908 343 8374
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/metrotrails/events/313683110/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260307T175103Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260307T175103Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
