SUMMARY:Cultural ARTS Series: New Jersey Symphony Chamber Trio
DESCRIPTION:Tonight’s featured performers hail from the distinguished New Jersey Symphony (NJS)\, which has been enriching communities through music since 1922. The NJS gave its very first concert right here in Montclair and has since evolved into a nationally recognized orchestra known for its artistic excellence and deep community engagement. \nThis concert will feature a woodwind trio: \nKathleen Nester\, flute\nBob Ingliss\, oboe\nJuan Esteban Martinez\, clarinet\n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n \n  \nProgram Details \nClaude Debussy – Syrinx\, for solo flute \nAntonio Vivaldi – Concerto in G Minor \nMalcolm Arnold – Divertimento for flute\, oboe\, clarinet \nAlberto Ginastera – Duo for flute and oboe \nRobert Muczyinski – Duo for flute and clarinet \nJohann Joachim Quantz – Trio Sonata in C Minor \n  \nTickets are required. There will be refreshments and a chance to ask the musicians questions.
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/cultural-arts-series-new-jersey-symphony-chamber-trio-2/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Events,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2026/03/Cultural-Arts-Series_March-21-2026-NJSO-Woodwind-Trio_updated.png
END:VEVENT
