SUMMARY:The Photographer's Eye: Developing Your Vision NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nPhotographer’s Eye is a relaxed\, beginner-friendly 
 photography course designed for adults who want to learn how to see and 
 take better pictures—no technical background required. Over two 3-hour 
 sessions (6 hours total)\, we’ll explore the basics of visual 
 storytelling\, composition\, light\, and how photographers make creative 
 choices. Through simple exercises\, discussion\, and image examples\, 
 participants will develop confidence and a stronger “photographic eye.” 
 Any camera is welcome\, including smartphones\, point-and-shoots\, or 
 DSLRs. Perfect for curious beginners and anyone looking to refresh their 
 perspective.\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Classroom\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Arts & Crafts
UID:LibCal-10306-15870885
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15870885
END:VEVENT
