SUMMARY:NEW DATE: Unsung Black Artists of Antebellum Era NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a free Adult School class. Registration is required. 
 Click here to register.\n\nDespite the trauma of enslavement\, racism and 
 segregation African American artists had their own forms of art. Join Onnie 
 Strother to explore how Black artists before Emancipation created\, 
 pottery\, quilts\, paintings and photographs\, which forged a tradition of 
 creativity and\nexcellence for future generations to follow. Among others\, 
 we'll survey the life and work of Augustus Washington\, Photographer\; 
 Henry Ossawa Tanner\, Painter\; Grafton Brown\, Painter\; Edmonia Lewis\, 
 Sculptor\; and David Drake\, Potter.\n\nMade possible by funds from the New 
 Jersey State Council on the Arts\, a partner agency of the National 
 Endowment for the Arts.\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-16586528
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16586528
END:VEVENT
