DESCRIPTION:Before the Flame: Voices in Action is an annual event organize
 d by the Student Government Association in honor of Women’s History Month
 . In its first installment\, this event will take place prior to the Cent
 er for Student Leadership & Engagement’s annual Igniting the Flame progra
 m. The event will feature faculty speakers from various disciplines who w
 ill share their experiences\, passions\, and perspectives on advocacy\, c
 ommunication\, and community leadership. Through a panel discussion and i
 nteractive breakout workshops\, attendees will explore strategies for nav
 igating conflict\, facilitating repair\, and advocating for themselves an
 d others both on and off campus. While the event centers the empowerment 
 and experiences of women\, who remain an oppressed class in society\, it 
 is free and open to all staff\, faculty\, and students. Participants will
  have opportunities to ask questions\, engage in guided discussions\, and
  practice real-world communication strategies that support equity\, accou
 ntability\, and collective growth.\n\nHosted by: Bloomfield College Stude
 nt Government Association (BCSGA)\, Bloomfield CAPS \n\nAdditional Inform
 ation can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/1234
 2057
DTEND:20260325T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260318T024951Z
DTSTART:20260325T180000Z
