SUMMARY:Midday MeetUp - Bonnie Rapp\, Best of Broadway
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260609T114500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260609T133000
DTSTAMP:20260313T210315Z
UID:TU2007101531
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20260609T114500
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20251214T005612Z
DESCRIPTION:**Midday MeetUp - Bonnie Rapp\, Best of Broadway   \nA monthly
  gathering to make connections and learn together.  \n11:45am Catered Lunc
 h (free)  \n12:30pm Featured Program   \n  \nExperience *The Best of Broad
 way* as Bonnie Rapp brings to life unforgettable moments from Tony Award
 –winning musicals. Relive the golden age of musical theatre through belo
 ved classics and timeless melodies by legendary composers such as Rodgers 
 and Hammerstein\, Lerner and Loewe\, Frank Loesser\, Irving Berlin and mor
 e!  \n  \nCost:** FREE or Suggested Donation of $10 per person to offset c
 osts. (Bill My Account is only open to Shomrei Members)  \n  \n**RSVP:** R
 equired so we know how much food to buy.  \nhttps://shomrei.easyshul.com/e
 vents/6967e6f2368f110026c0c486  \n  \n**\\***Members &amp\; PreSchool Fami
 lies should use their fob to access the building.  \n About Bonnie Rapp** 
  \nBonnie had the honor of performing the lead role of Christine Daaé in 
 the National Tour/San Francisco Company of Andrew Lloyd Webber's The Phant
 om of the Opera. Some of Bonnie’s favorite roles include Maria in The So
 und of Music\, Kate in Kiss Me\, Kate\, Cinderella in Rodgers and Hammerst
 ein’s Cinderella\, Louise in Gypsy and Sister Amnesia and Sister Leo in 
 Nunsense\, Nunsense II and Nunsense Jamboree. In addition\, Bonnie has app
 eared in numerous galas\, fundraisers\, and Broadway concerts\, including 
 performances at Lincoln Center's Avery Fisher Hall.  \n  \nFor the past de
 cade\, Bonnie has devoted her talents to providing live musical entertainm
 ent for a wide range of audiences\, including corporate and community even
 ts\, libraries\, private celebrations\, JCCs\, and residents of independen
 t living\, assisted living\, nursing homes\, and memory care communities. 
  \n  \nFull_Season_Schedule_for_Midday_MeetUps: https://shomrei.org/calend
 ar/midday-meetup-calendar  \n  \n**Questions?** Contact June Zimmerman\,  
  \nVP for Programming  \njzimmerman@shomrei.org  \n  \n\\#middaymeetup\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20260212T223312Z
LOCATION:Social Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
